text: Hurricane Hermine was a tropical cyclone in August and September 2016. It affected states from Florida to New England. The storm hit Florida on September 1, near the Big Bend region. Hermine had winds of 80 miles per hour at landfall. The storm also struck Georgia, South Carolina and North Carolina. Hermine was expected to affect areas from Virginia to Massachusetts and Rhode Island. At least two deaths were blamed on the storm. ==References== Category:2016 in the United States Category:August 2016 events Category:Hurricanes in the United States Category:September 2016 events Category:2016 Atlantic hurricane season
